OL,7,FBut, individuals who have weaker
OL,8,Fimmune systems or are older, have
OL,9,Fcomplex medical conditions, pregnant
OL,10,Fwomen and children under five are at a
OL,11,Fgreater risk of complications such as
OL,12,Fsepsis.
OL,14,FIt is spread by contact with
OL,15,Fcontaminated faeces, either directly
OL,16,Fthrough person-to-person transmission
OL,17,For indirectly from food and water
OL,18,Fcontaminated with the bacteria.
